rpretation associated with Carson and her work, the book gives readers a more accurate sense of the past and better prepares them for thinking and acting in the present.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aEnvironmentalismzUnited StatesxHistory. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh  a1960s.  a19th century.  aacademic.  aamerican history.  aamerican literature.  acommunity.  aeconomy.  aenvironment.  aenvironmental history.  aenvironmental problems.  aenvironmentalism.  aenvironmentalist.  aexploitation.  aindustrial revolution.  aindustry.  ainequality.  alabor union.  amodern world.  aoppression.  aprotest.  aprotestor.  ascholarly.  asocial studies.  aunited states.  aus history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831106676770 cprintz978052029133140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096515740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520965157423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520965157/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles